extends ../../layouts/layout-beta.pug

block content
  #content.section--primary
    .container
      h1 Object to the High Speed Rail (West Midlands – Crewe) Bill

      br
      .status--highlight
        p The deadline is 5pm on 9 January 2018.

  section
    .container
      h2 Overview

      p Any individual, group of individuals, organisation or group of organisations affected by the High Speed Rail (West Midlands – Crewe) Bill can object to it.

      p To find out more about the bill, visit the #[+link('https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/high-speed-two-limited', 'HS2 Ltd website')].

  section
    .container
      h2 Objecting to the bill

      p To object to the High Speed Rail (West Midlands – Crewe) Bill you will need to download and complete our petition template.

      p We will ask for your name, address and examples of how you are affected by the bill.

      p The petition does not require any signatures.

  section
    .container
      h2 Contact details

      p We will ask you to tell us who should be contacted about your petition. This main contact can be you or someone else, for example a friend, family member or lawyer.

      p The main contact will receive all petition communications. They will usually be invited to give evidence about it to the  #[+link('http://www.parliament.uk/business/committees/committees-a-z/commons-select/high-speed-rail-west-midlands-crewe-bill-select-committee-commons', 'High Speed Rail (West Midlands – Crewe) Bill Committee')].

  section
    .container
      h2 After sending your petition

      .track--alternative
        h3.typography--light Once we’ve received your petition we’ll ask you to pay a &pound;20 admin fee.

        h3.typography--light We will publish your petition on our website. This will include your name and address.

        h3.typography--light We’ll send your petition to HS2 Ltd, who may contact you to discuss it. HS2 Ltd can challenge your petition if they don’t believe you are affected by the bill.

        h3.typography--light You will usually be invited to give evidence to the committee about your petition. Hearings are scheduled for spring 2018.

      .section--major
        +buttonLink('page03.html', 'Petition on our website', 'btn--primary')
        +buttonLink('page02.html', 'Petition by email, post or in person', 'btn--primary--inverse')
